In like manner this Enſuing Sermon containing one great end of the Goſpel of Chriſt, viz. That all Chriſtians ſhould Serve the Lord in Holineſs and Righteouſneſs before Him all the dayes of our lives,


Luke 1.75. It is now preſented to Your Self as to our moſt Excellent Theophilus in concurrence with all New England, bowing down themſelves before You as to our Governour ſent from God and the King. We give thanks to God for Your ſafe Arrival;
Per varios Caſus, Per tot diſcrimina rerum.
